## 7. Word Break (LC 139)

**Problem:** Given string `s` and dictionary `wordDict`, return true if `s` can be segmented into a sequence of one or more dictionary words.

**Examples:**

```
s="leetcode", wordDict=["leet","code"]  -> true
s="applepenapple", wordDict=["apple","pen"]  -> true
s="catsandog", wordDict=["cats","dog","sand","and","cat"]  -> false
```

### The DP Insight

`dp[i]` is true if `s[0..i-1]` (the first i characters) can be segmented using dictionary words.

**Base case:** `dp[0] = true`. The empty prefix needs zero words, trivially valid.

**Transition:** `dp[i] = true` if there exists `j < i` such that `dp[j] = true` AND `s[j..i-1]` is a dictionary word. Intuition: if the prefix up to `j` is already valid, and the remaining segment from `j` to `i-1` is a whole word, then the prefix up to `i` is valid too.

```cpp
bool wordBreak(string s, vector<string>& wordDict) {
    unordered_set<string> dict(wordDict.begin(), wordDict.end());
    int n = s.size();
    vector<bool> dp(n + 1, false);
    dp[0] = true;

    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
            if (dp[j] && dict.count(s.substr(j, i - j))) {
                dp[i] = true;
                break;
            }
        }
    }
    return dp[n];
}
```

Time: O(n squared times L) where L is the max word length (substring extraction cost). Space: O(n) for `dp` plus dictionary storage.

### Dry Run: s="leetcode", wordDict=["leet","code"]

```
dict={"leet","code"}
dp = [T,F,F,F,F,F,F,F,F]  (indices 0..8)

i=1: j=0: "l" not in dict. dp[1]=F.
i=2: j=0: "le" no. j=1: dp[1]=F. dp[2]=F.
i=3: j=0: "lee" no. dp[3]=F.
i=4: j=0: dp[0]=T, "leet" IN dict! dp[4]=T. break.
i=5: j=0..3: no. j=4: dp[4]=T, "c" no. dp[5]=F.
i=6: j=4: dp[4]=T, "co" no. dp[6]=F.
i=7: j=4: dp[4]=T, "cod" no. dp[7]=F.
i=8: j=4: dp[4]=T, "code" IN dict! dp[8]=T. break.

Return dp[8] = true
```

### Optimization: Iterate Over Word Lengths

Instead of checking every `j < i`, only check `j` values where `i - j` equals a length that exists in the dictionary:

```cpp
bool wordBreak(string s, vector<string>& wordDict) {
    unordered_set<string> dict(wordDict.begin(), wordDict.end());
    unordered_set<int> wordLens;
    for (auto& w : wordDict) wordLens.insert(w.size());

    int n = s.size();
    vector<bool> dp(n + 1, false);
    dp[0] = true;

    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        for (int len : wordLens) {
            if (len <= i && dp[i - len] && dict.count(s.substr(i - len, len))) {
                dp[i] = true;
                break;
            }
        }
    }
    return dp[n];
}
```

Time: O(n times W) where W is the number of distinct word lengths, typically much smaller than n.

