## 9. Edge Cases

| Problem | Input | Expected | Reason |
|---|---|---|---|
| Sliding Window Max | `[1]`, k=1 | `[1]` | Single element |
| Sliding Window Max | k = array length | Single max value | Only one window exists |
| Stock Span | All increasing prices | Spans = 1,2,3,4,... | Each price absorbs all previous |
| Stock Span | All decreasing prices | Spans all = 1 | Stack never pops |
| Celebrity | All know each other | -1 | No one knows nobody |
| Celebrity | n=2 | 0 or 1 or -1 | Depends on the single pairwise relation |
| LRU | put on existing key at capacity | No eviction | Update plus move to front, no new node created |
| LRU | capacity = 0 | Always returns -1, never stores | Some implementations special-case this |
| LFU | capacity = 0 | put does nothing | Guard: `if (cap == 0) return;` |
| LFU | Tie in frequency | Evict the least recently used among them | freqMap DLL ordering handles this naturally |
| Word Break | Empty dictionary | false unless s is empty | dp[0]=true but no transitions possible |
| Word Break | s itself is a dictionary word | true | dp[n] reachable directly from dp[0] |

