## 12. Quick Revision Cheat Sheet

**Sliding Window Maximum, Monotonic Deque**

```cpp
deque<int> dq;   // stores INDICES, values decreasing front-to-back
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    if (!dq.empty() && dq.front() == i-k) dq.pop_front();           // expire (use ==)
    while (!dq.empty() && nums[dq.back()] <= nums[i]) dq.pop_back(); // remove useless
    dq.push_back(i);
    if (i >= k-1) result.push_back(nums[dq.front()]);
}
```

Front equals window max. O(n) amortized; each index enters/exits at most once.

---

**Stock Span, Monotonic Stack with Accumulated Span**

```cpp
stack<pair<int,int>> st;  // {price, accumulated_span}
int next(int price) {
    int span = 1;
    while (!st.empty() && st.top().first <= price) { span += st.top().second; st.pop(); }
    st.push({price, span});
    return span;
}
```

Pop entries less than or equal to current price, absorb their spans. O(n) amortized.

---

**Celebrity Problem, Eliminate and Verify**

```cpp
int candidate = 0;
for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) if (knows(candidate, i)) candidate = i;
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    if (i == candidate) continue;
    if (!knows(i, candidate) || knows(candidate, i)) return -1;
}
return candidate;
```

Phase 1: O(n) elimination. Phase 2: O(n) verification (mandatory).

---

**LRU Cache, HashMap + DLL**

```
head (MRU sentinel) <-> ... <-> tail (LRU sentinel)
removeNode: 2 pointer updates (left and right neighbors reconnect)
insertAfterHead: 4 pointer updates
get: remove + insertAfterHead + return value
put: exists -> update + remove + insertAfterHead
     new + full -> remove tail->prev, erase from map, insert new after head
```

O(1) per operation. Always update HashMap and DLL together.

---

**LFU Cache, Two HashMaps + Multiple DLLs**

```
keyMap:  key -> Node*
freqMap: freq -> DLL*
minFreq: tracks minimum frequency for O(1) eviction

updateFreq(node):
  remove from freqMap[node->freq]
  if that DLL is now empty AND freq == minFreq: minFreq++
  node->freq++
  insert into freqMap[node->freq] (create DLL if needed)

put new key: minFreq = 1; insert into freqMap[1]
evict: removeLast() from freqMap[minFreq]; erase from keyMap
```

---

**Word Break, 1D DP**

```cpp
dp[0] = true;
for i = 1..n: for j = 0..i-1:
    if dp[j] && s[j..i-1] in dict: dp[i] = true; break;
return dp[n];
```

`dp[i]` means: can `s[0..i-1]` be segmented. Base case `dp[0]=true` is mandatory.

---

**Key Facts**

```
Monotonic deque invariant: front = window max; values decrease front-to-back.
                            Front expires when index == i-k (use == not <).
                            Back elements removed when value <= incoming element.

Stock Span shortcut:       pop entries <= current price, absorb their spans.
                            Correct because absorbed days can never be a boundary
                            for any future price >= current.

Celebrity elimination:     knows(a,b)=true -> eliminate a.
                            knows(a,b)=false -> eliminate b.
                            ALWAYS verify the surviving candidate.

LRU sentinels:              Eliminate all null-pointer edge cases.
                            insertAfterHead = 4 pointers. removeNode = 2 pointers.
                            Update HashMap and DLL together, every time.

LFU minFreq rules:          Reset to 1 only on new key insertion.
                            Increment only when freqMap[minFreq] becomes empty
                            after a frequency upgrade. Never decrements.

Word Break dp[0]:           Must be true; empty string needs 0 words, trivially valid.
```
